## Bug #2 Fixed: Post-Payment Plan Refresh

After Stripe payment, the UI showed "Free Plan" because the JWT in localStorage still had `plan: free`.

### Changes Made

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [auth.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/routes/auth.js) | Added `GET /api/auth/me` — returns fresh user data + new JWT from DB |
| [api.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/services/api.js) | Added [fetchCurrentUser()](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/services/api.js#150-160) — calls `/api/auth/me`, saves to localStorage |
| [AuthContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/context/AuthContext.jsx) | Added [refreshUser()](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#49-59) method exposed in context |
| [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx) | Detects `?upgrade=success` → auto-calls [refreshUser()](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#49-59) |

### Flow
```
Stripe redirect → /dashboard?upgrade=success
  → Dashboard useEffect detects param
  → calls refreshUser()
  → GET /api/auth/me returns { plan: "pro", token: "..." }
  → AuthContext updates state
  → UI shows "Pro Plan", removes upgrade buttons
```

